    <briefdescription>
<para><ref refid="classwx_help_controller_help_provider" kindref="compound">wxHelpControllerHelpProvider</ref> is an implementation of <ref refid="classwx_help_provider" kindref="compound">wxHelpProvider</ref> which supports both context identifiers and plain text help strings. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>If the help text is an integer, it is passed to <ref refid="classwx_help_controller_base_1a8ec7169cdc87678e2bbee7f1c6a8cdca" kindref="member">wxHelpController::DisplayContextPopup()</ref>. Otherwise, it shows the string in a tooltip as per <ref refid="classwx_simple_help_provider" kindref="compound">wxSimpleHelpProvider</ref>. If you use this with a wxCHMHelpController instance on windows, it will use the native style of tip window instead of <ref refid="classwx_tip_window" kindref="compound">wxTipWindow</ref>.</para>
<para>You can use the convenience function wxContextId() to convert an integer context id to a string for passing to <ref refid="classwx_window_1a4c1a2cbc7363237b3a7c70af4e702c72" kindref="member">wxWindow::SetHelpText()</ref>.</para>
<para><heading level="2"></heading>
</para>
<para>Library:<nonbreakablespace/><nonbreakablespace/><ref refid="page_libs_1page_libs_wxcore" kindref="member">wxCore</ref> &lt;&gt;&lt; =&apos;&apos;&gt;:&lt;/&gt;&amp;;&amp;;&lt; =&apos;&apos;&gt;\ &lt;/&gt;&lt;/&gt;</para>
<para><simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classwx_help_provider" kindref="compound">wxHelpProvider</ref>, <ref refid="classwx_simple_help_provider" kindref="compound">wxSimpleHelpProvider</ref>, <ref refid="classwx_context_help" kindref="compound">wxContextHelp</ref>, <ref refid="classwx_window_1a4c1a2cbc7363237b3a7c70af4e702c72" kindref="member">wxWindow::SetHelpText()</ref>, <ref refid="classwx_window_1a7d11a419fede5049d7c12c337e5f5dfc" kindref="member">wxWindow::GetHelpTextAtPoint()</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
